trans-unit.source: HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERR: Raised if a DocumentType node would be extracted into the new DocumentFragment.

trans-unit.source: HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERR: Raised if an attempt is made to add a node doesn't belong in this NamedNodeMap. Examples would include trying to insert something other than an Attr node into an Element's map of attributes, or a non-Entity node into the DocumentType's map of Entities.

trans-unit.source: HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERR: Raised if the container of the start of the Range is of a type that does not allow children of the type of newNode or if newNode is an ancestor of the container.
trans-unit.target: HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERR：如果Range开头的容器的类型不允许 newNode 类型的子级，或者 newNode 是该容器的祖先，则引发此错误。

trans-unit.source: HIERARCHY_REQUEST_ERR: Raised if the container of the start of the Range is of a type that does not allow children of the type of newParent or if newParent is an ancestor of the container or if node would end up with a child node of a type not allowed by the type of node.

trans-unit.source: HTML provides a well known set of features without exactly specifying the display characteristics. Swing has a theme mechanism for its look-and-feel implementations. trans-unit.source: HTML.Attributes defines a type safe enumeration of html attributes. If an attribute key of a tag is defined in HTML.Attribute, the HTML.Attribute will be used as the key, otherwise a String will be used. For example <p foo=bar class=neat> has two attributes. foo is not defined in HTML.Attribute, where as class is, therefore the AttributeSet will have two values in it, HTML.Attribute.CLASS with a String value of 'neat' and the String key 'foo' with a String value of 'bar'.
trans-unit.target: HTML.Attributes定义html属性的类型安全枚举。如果在HTML.Attribute中定义了标签的属性键，则将HTML.Attribute用作键，否则将使用String。例如，<p foo = bar class = neat>具有两个属性。在HTML.Attribute中未定义foo，而在class中是foo，因此AttributeSet中将包含两个值，即HTML.Attribute.CLASS，其String值为“整洁”，以及字符串键“ foo”，其String值为“酒吧'。
